				<h1> pubmedBatch <small>a Pubmed harassing app :)</small></h2>
				<br/>
				<p> Please visit the <a href="https://github.com/logust79/pubmedBatch"><b>github</b></a> for details.</p>
				<ul>
					<li>The csv file is required to have a column with genes you want to query on Pubmed. The app also recognises columns with headers like <b>FILTER</b> and <b>*Pred</b>, although they are not required to run the app.</li>
					<li>You may also provide a list of genes to highlight (in green) in the result. The gene names in the file should be separated with white spaces.</li>
					<li>You may also provide a blacklist of gene names you don't want the app to query Pubmed. The gene names in the file should be separated with white spaces.</li>
					<li>In order to speed up the query, repetitive searching terms are stored in a SQLite database, which will be saved for 14 days by default. This can be changed in the <i>life</i> field in the <i>config.yml</i></li>
					<li><b>Verbose</b> mode will give all data back. Non-verbose mode will only give back results with positive Pubmed score.</li>
					<li>"OR" terms and the gene name will be queried to <b>[All Fields]</b>, whereas "AND" terms will be queried to <b>[Title/Abstract]</b>.</li>
					<li>Pubmed score is calculated by the number of appearance of the "OR" terms in the <b>[Title/Abstract]</b> fields.</li>
					<li>If the quality of the variance call (the column with the <b>FILTER</b> header) is <b>PASS</b>, the "Del row" button is coloured green: <button class="btn btn-sm btn-success">Del row</button>. If it is <b>FAIL</b>, the button is coloured red: <button class="btn btn-sm btn-danger">Del row</button>. Otherwise the button is yellow: <button class="btn btn-sm btn-warning">Del row</button>. If no column in the csv file has the FILTER header, all buttons will be coloured green.</li>
					<li>Pred score is calculated by considering the <b>[*Pred]</b> fields. [D/A].each = 10, [P].each = 5, [C].each = 6, [T/B/N].each = -1. If there is a splicing/insertion/deletion event, the score is set as 1000. Not given is set as 0. If no *Pred field is available, it will give 0 as the value.</li>
				</ul>
